---
/**
 * Homelab — a deep dive on the flagship project: the self-hosted Kubernetes
 * platform that serves this site. Prose in Henry's own register (see
 * writing_style.md), tracing the system concretely; the live, interactive
 * topology lives on the home page (#infra) and availability on /status.
 */
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

// The notes are write-ups about this platform, listed here (drafts excluded,
// newest first) rather than in a peer top-level section.
const notes = (await getCollection('writing', ({ data }) => !data.draft)).sort(
  (a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf(),
);
const fmtNote = (d: Date) =>
  d.toLocaleDateString('en-IE', { year: 'numeric', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });

const stack: [string, string][] = [
  ['Host', 'Proxmox VE on an i5-14500T · 24 GB RAM · ZFS RAID-1 (2×2 TB)'],
  ['Cluster', 'Two-node k3s (control + worker VMs) on the single host'],
  ['Edge', 'Cloudflare Tunnel (no forwarded ports) · Traefik ingress · MetalLB · cert-manager'],
  ['GitOps', 'ArgoCD (app-of-apps) reconciling a git repo · Sealed Secrets · Gitea'],
  ['Storage', 'ZFS RAID-1 mirror (redundancy at the block layer) · Longhorn volumes'],
  ['Observability', 'VictoriaMetrics · Grafana · Alertmanager'],
  ['Backup', 'restic → Backblaze B2, nightly, off-site (encrypted)'],
  ['Apps', 'Nextcloud · Immich · Collabora · Kiwix · Gitea · this site'],
];
---

<Base
  wide
  title="Homelab — Henry Dowd"
  description="A deep dive on the self-hosted, two-node Kubernetes platform that serves this site: Proxmox, k3s, ArgoCD GitOps, and full observability, all reconciled from a single git repository."
>
  <PageNav current="homelab" />
  <article class="lab">
    <nav class="lab__rail" aria-label="On this page">
      <ol class="lab__index">
        <li><a href="#how">How it works</a></li>
        <li><a href="#stack">The stack</a></li>
        <li><a href="#notes">Notes</a></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="lab__railnote">Live topology and status live on the <a href="/">home page</a>.</p>
    </nav>
    <div class="lab__body">
    <header class="lab__head">
      <p class="lab__kicker">The platform this page runs on</p>
      <h1>Homelab platform</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A two-node Kubernetes cluster that I run at home, on a single machine
        under my desk, and that I manage entirely from one git repository; it
        hosts a dozen or so services my household genuinely uses, and it also
        serves this very page, which is then scraped by the same monitoring the
        page reports on.
      </p>
      <p class="lab__links">
        <a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/homelab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Config repo ↗</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/portfolio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">This site's source ↗</a>
        <a href="/status/">Live status →</a>
        <a href="/#infra">Live topology →</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <section id="how" class="lab__sec lab__prose">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Everything runs on one Proxmox host, and on top of it sit two virtual
        machines that make up a k3s cluster, a control node and a worker. Nothing
        in that cluster is changed by me editing it live. The git repository is the
        single source of truth, ArgoCD watches it and continuously reconciles the
        running state back towards whatever is committed using the "app of apps"
        pattern. Adding a service is a commit and a push, not a manual change,
        and the deploys that come out of it are reviewable and repeatable.
        That discipline, rather than the scale, is the point of running it this way,
        and it is the part that carries straight over to real work. One machine does
        mean one of everything, a single host and a single uplink. The night
        that network card wedged itself and took the whole homelab dark is written
        up in the <a href="/homelab/notes/nic-hang/">notes below</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        No web request from the public internet lands on a forwarded port, because
        there is not one open for them. Each arrives over a Cloudflare tunnel that a
        daemon holds open from the inside, and Traefik terminates it and routes it on
        while MetalLB hands out the addresses the services answer on. The one port I
        do forward is for my own WireGuard VPN, so I can still get back in when the
        cluster is down. Inside the house the same names resolve locally through
        <a href="/homelab/notes/split-horizon-dns/">split-horizon DNS</a>, so LAN
        traffic never leaves the building. Behind the ingress the services keep their
        state on Longhorn volumes, with the redundancy for those and for everything
        else on the box sitting underneath in a
        <a href="/homelab/notes/zfs-mirror/">ZFS mirror</a> rather than in replica
        copies inside a single-machine cluster. The credentials they need are
        committed to the same public repository but sealed so only the cluster can
        read them, and the whole lot is scraped by the VictoriaMetrics, Grafana and
        Alertmanager stack that also monitors this page. The only path that leaves
        the host is the backup, restic pushing an encrypted copy off-site to Backblaze
        every night, which covers the failures a local mirror cannot, theft, fire, or
        a fat-fingered delete.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="stack" class="lab__sec">
      <h2>The stack</h2>
      <dl class="lab__stack">
        {stack.map(([k, v]) => (
          <div><dt>{k}</dt><dd>{v}</dd></div>
        ))}
      </dl>
    </section>

    {notes.length > 0 && (
      <section id="notes" class="lab__sec" aria-label="Notes">
        <h2>Notes</h2>
        <p class="lab__notesintro">
          Longer write-ups of things I built or debugged here, from the reasoning
          behind a decision to a post-mortem of something that broke.
        </p>
        <ul class="lab__notes">
          {notes.map(({ id, data }) => (
            <li>
              <a href={`/homelab/notes/${id}/`}>
                <span class="lab__note-t">{data.title}</span>
                <span class="lab__note-d">{data.description}</span>
                <time class="lab__note-date" datetime={data.date.toISOString()}>{fmtNote(data.date)}</time>
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>
    )}
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .lab { font-family: var(--sans); }
  /* Reading column, centred like the other subpages until the rail appears. */
  .lab__body { max-width: var(--measure); margin-inline: auto; }

  /* Left rail: a sticky section index, matching the home page's rail. Hidden
     below the breakpoint (same as home); the body then reads as a single column. */
  .lab__rail { display: none; }
  .lab__index { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; padding: 0; }
  .lab__index li { padding: 0.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .lab__index li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .lab__index a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s ease; }
  .lab__index a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .lab__railnote { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .lab__railnote a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .lab__railnote a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (min-width: 74rem) {
    /* The reading column stays centred in the frame exactly like the other
       pages (equal 1fr gutters either side of the measure); the rail floats out
       into the left gutter rather than being centred together with the content. */
    .lab {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, var(--measure)) minmax(0, 1fr);
      align-items: start;
    }
    .lab__body { grid-column: 2; }
    .lab__rail {
      display: block; grid-column: 1; justify-self: end;
      width: 11rem; margin-right: 1.75rem;
      position: sticky; top: 1.5rem; font-family: var(--mono);
    }
  }

  /* Anchor targets clear the sticky offset a little when jumped to. */
  #how, #stack, #notes { scroll-margin-top: 1.5rem; }

  .lab__head { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .lab__kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
  }
  .lab__head h1 { font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.4rem); margin: 0 0 1rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.05; }
  .lab .lede {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.6vw, 1.6rem);
    line-height: 1.45; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .lab__links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.8rem 1.5rem; margin: 0; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem; }
  .lab__links a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .lab__links a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  /* The narrative section is a .lab__sec (chrome + heading); .lab__prose only
     sets its serif paragraph typography. */
  .lab__prose p {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.18rem; line-height: 1.62; margin: 0 0 1.3rem;
  }
  .lab__prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .lab__prose a { color: var(--accent); text-underline-offset: 3px; }

  .lab__sec { padding: 1.75rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .lab__sec > h2 {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }
  .lab__stack div {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 10rem) 1fr; gap: 0.4rem 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .lab__stack div:first-child { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
  .lab__stack dt {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0;
  }
  .lab__stack dd { margin: 0; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; }

  .lab__notesintro { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .lab__notes { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .lab__notes li { border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .lab__notes li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .lab__notes a { display: block; padding: 1.1rem 0; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; }
  .lab__note-t {
    display: block; font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .lab__notes a:hover .lab__note-t { color: var(--accent); }
  .lab__note-d { display: block; font-size: 0.98rem; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-top: 0.35rem; }
  .lab__note-date {
    display: block; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-top: 0.5rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
</style>
